The paper proposes a model for semi-supervised learning on people-centric sensing data, which involves recognizing human intentions, activities, muscular movements, and gestures. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a model for learning from labeled and unlabeled data, and evaluating it on real-world datasets.
